{{Quote|You ever do the Belsavis Run, Han? There's a spot in the southern hemisphere that's far enough from any rift or vent to be atmospherically stable every twenty-four hours. The Corridor, it's called. Because of the storms and the ionization in the upper atmosphere they can't track anyone that's not coming down a charted beam. You come in high, drop fast, and run along close to the ice to one of the pads.|[[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] to [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="Children of the Jedi (novel)">[[Children of the Jedi (novel)|''Children of the Jedi'']]</ref>}}
'''The Corridor''' was an area on [[Belsavis/Legends|Belsavis]]' southern hemisphere. It was far enough from the world's volcanic vents to be atmospherically stable every twenty-four hours. Because the authorities could not track ships passing through it, it was used as a haunt for [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]] making the [[Belsavis Run]]. [[Drub McKumb]] had been one of the people who operated it.

